forEach

Type: Array method
Usage: Iterates over each element of an array and executes a callback function for each element
Cannot use break or continue inside it
Does not return a value (always returns undefined)

When to use it:

When you want to perform an action on each element only
You don’t need to stop the loop early

------------------
for...of

Type: Loop over arrays, strings, or any iterable
Can use break and continue
Can work with await inside async functions

When to use it:

When you need flexibility to stop or skip elements
When you want a more general loop
Works with any iterable (array, string, Map, Set...)

