/*
try...catch is used to handle errors in JavaScript.

The try block runs the code that might throw an error.
If an error happens, the catch block runs and lets us handle the error without breaking the program
The finally block (optional) always runs, whether there was an error or not.

why it is important in async operations?

In async code, promises or await can fail.
Using try-catch prevents the program from crashing and lets us handle the error gracefully.
